<table  border=0 cellpadding=2 cellspacing=0 awidth=100%><a name=100268847649291></a><form action=http://eqdb.allakhazam.com/strategy/mrate.pl name=f100268847649291><tr><td id=headerrow><a id=sj href=classes.html?class=6&mid=100268847649291>RE: Spells</a> <a id=fs8 href=classes.html?class=6&mid=100268847649291#post><img src=http://everquest.allakhazam.com/static/reply.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=16 width=16></a></td><td align=right id=headerrow valign=bottom><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=52529><span id=Scholar>Ryanlynx</span></a>, <span id=Scholar>Scholar</span><br><span id=notbold>65 posts</td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Wed, Oct 10th 12:34 AM 2001</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Decent<span id=notbold>[3.07]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>If you cant find the spells in the Hall of Truth, they will be in the Temple of Love. There hard to find because the Temple of Love has ALOT of spell merchants, on different floors, on opposite sides of the floor, and each level of spell seems to be sold by two different merchants.<br>The only exception will be Divine Purpose, which is sold in Iceclad Ocean (need Velious) at the gnome camp.<br>Endure disease can also be quested (if you still cant find it) In Qeynos Hills there are rabid bears, killing one will drop a putrid bear hide (watch out for Holly though), give the hide to one of the clerics in the Temple of Life (the ufo, the npc will ask for the hides when hailed)<br>Thurgadin (sp) has all the spells from lvl 9 to 22 that I've seen, the rest are prolly sold in the cleric guild<br>&nbsp;<br>Ryanlynx<br>Paladin of Mith Marr<br>Xev<br><br>"Honor before Humility and all that jazz."</td></tr>
