<table  border=0 cellpadding=2 cellspacing=0 awidth=100%><a name=100231040717545></a><form action=http://eqdb.allakhazam.com/strategy/mrate.pl name=f100231040717545><tr><td id=headerrow><a id=sj href=classes.html?class=6&mid=100231040717545>RE: Low level Dwarven Paladin needs advice</a> <a id=fs8 href=classes.html?class=6&mid=100231040717545#post><img src=http://everquest.allakhazam.com/static/reply.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=16 width=16></a></td><td align=right id=headerrow valign=bottom><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=20703><span id= >Torsk</span></a>, <span id= > </span><br><span id=notbold>208 posts</td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Fri, Oct 5th 3:33 PM 2001</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Decent<span id=notbold>[2.99]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>If you are currently sporting leather armour, then a good upgrade is to "/auction WTB Banded Armour, size small" It should sell for 1pp per ac, is player made & will serve you very well as you upgrade from banded to bronze(which is dropped off critters), then fs plate (which is again player made)and then finally around level 30+ you will be picking up ( from killing critters like the undead knight in unrest, some magical armour like Bloodstained Mantle or bp) or buying it in /auction mode. <br>I always keep auction open, in case i see a good weapon or piece of armour that is an upgrade for me, that i can afford.<br>I think i went from leather to ringmail or chainmail, then when i learned about banded i regretted getting the mail. Banded is cheaper , lighter & higher ac .<br>High level smiths do not like to make banded arfmour, for young players because it is not profitable & takes a lot of time. Unless you befreind a high level smith , or your guild has a few. <br>Work your smithy skill, when you have lots of excess plat. If you find yourself with lots of time & little cash. you can still work it up the hard way, just check out the guidlines that are available. There are a few really good ones that tell you the cheap way to raise skill that takes tons of time, and the fast way to skill up that takes lots of plat. Good luck. I stopped smithing at skill 180 because the i just lost too much plat making fs plate, altho there was a time that I made a small fortune at it. (I changed my armour & stats & my fail rate increased substatially)<br>Player made fs plate generally sells for 10pp per ac for 1 sheet items. Aface plate is say 60pp , 2 sheet items sell for 130pp + And 3 sheet items sell for 200pp+. I used to sell fs plate bp for 250pp, legs 225pp cloak 225pp.<br>With my current armour configuration, I have failed 15 out the last 18 attempts at making 2 & 3 sheet items, so naturally i am not doing much smithing these days. I will again some day as I have 3 earthen tempers in the bank & i really want to make some dwarven cultural armor some day!<br>Hope this was helpful & answered some of your questions!<br>Torsk Holynite, Ad Gloriam<br>Dwarf Paladin of the 50th Season<br>Lanys T'Vyl<br>&nbsp;<br></td></tr>
